A [[Function]] is said to be ''linear'' if it satisfies"

$$f(\alpha x + \beta y) = \alpha f(x) + \beta f(y)$$

for all $$x, y \in \mathbf{R}^n$$ and all $$\alpha, \beta \in \mathbf{R}$$.